## Quickstart

```bash
docker compose up -d
# first run: wait for the `ollama-pull` service to download the model (several GB)
docker compose logs -f ollama-pull
```

Open `http://localhost:3000` to chat (open-webui), or `http://localhost:8000/docs` for the API.

## Ingest documents

```bash
curl -F "file=@./data/sample.pdf" http://localhost:8000/ingest
```

## Query

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/query \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"question": "What is RAG?"}'
```

## Evaluate retrieval quality

```bash
# edit eval/datasets/retrieval-golden.jsonl with real questions + relevant sources
perfectrag eval --retrieval -d eval/datasets/retrieval-golden.jsonl --gate
```

Reports recall@k / MRR / nDCG; `--gate` exits non-zero below thresholds (CI gate).

## Add MCP tool

```bash
perfectrag add mcp filesystem --project .
```

See `mcp.yaml` for configuration. Available MCP servers: `perfectrag list mcp`.

## Add skill

```bash
perfectrag add skill legal-rag --project .
```

Skills are mounted read-only into the `app` container.
